WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:01.168 --> 00:00:03.837
[♪ acoustic guitar playing]

2
00:00:09.676 --> 00:00:10.760
[tab clicks]

3
00:00:10.761 --> 00:00:13.931
[♪ "Yahoos and Triangles"
by The Refreshments playing]

4
00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:21.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

5
00:00:27.069 --> 00:00:29.071
♪

6
00:00:36.036 --> 00:00:37.119
[♪ theme song concludes]

7
00:00:37.120 --> 00:00:39.330
- [♪ gentle guitar music playing]
- [birds chirping]

8
00:00:39.331 --> 00:00:41.290
[coffee trickling]

9
00:00:41.291 --> 00:00:42.375
[Peggy yawning]

10
00:00:42.376 --> 00:00:43.377
[Hank blowing]

11
00:00:46.463 --> 00:00:48.798
Ugh. Gotdangit.

12
00:00:48.799 --> 00:00:50.424
- Peggy!
- What is it?

13
00:00:50.425 --> 00:00:52.343
- Look.
- Oh. Hank.

14
00:00:52.344 --> 00:00:55.346
No one is gonna judge your lawn
for uneven edging.

15
00:00:55.347 --> 00:00:58.307
Our lawn will always have perfect edges.

16
00:00:58.308 --> 00:01:00.434
You remember my wedding vows.

17
00:01:00.435 --> 00:01:02.436
I'm talkin' about the eyesore

18
00:01:02.437 --> 00:01:04.897
that's been parked out front
since last night.

19
00:01:04.898 --> 00:01:08.025
And?
It is not against the law to park here.

20
00:01:08.026 --> 00:01:10.152
This is bigger than the law. Peggy.

21
00:01:10.153 --> 00:01:12.321
It's about common decency.

22
00:01:12.322 --> 00:01:15.366
You don't think you're being
just a tad ridiculous?

23
00:01:15.367 --> 00:01:17.660
No. it's blocking the number on the curb.

24
00:01:17.661 --> 00:01:21.163
When you're chokin' on a grape
and the paramedics can't find our house.

25
00:01:21.164 --> 00:01:23.833
then we can talk about
who's being ridiculous.

26
00:01:23.834 --> 00:01:27.628
Hank. come on.
What is really bothering you?

27
00:01:27.629 --> 00:01:30.756
I don't want anyone
to think that's my truck.

28
00:01:30.757 --> 00:01:33.259
It's... electric.

29
00:01:33.260 --> 00:01:36.178
Oh. Hank. no reasonable person

30
00:01:36.179 --> 00:01:38.806
is going to think <i>you</i>
bought an electric vehicle.

31
00:01:38.807 --> 00:01:40.309
[doorbell ringing]

32
00:01:41.977 --> 00:01:44.895
Please. tell me you didn't buy
an electric truck.

33
00:01:44.896 --> 00:01:46.731
I said "reasonable."

34
00:01:46.732 --> 00:01:48.691
It's not my truck. Bill.

35
00:01:48.692 --> 00:01:51.278
It's some inconsiderate interloper's.

36
00:01:52.821 --> 00:01:54.947
Ah. man. them times have been
dang ol' changin'. man.

37
00:01:54.948 --> 00:01:57.908
Little bit talkin' about Bob Dylan
goin' electric. but-- but worse. man.

38
00:01:57.909 --> 00:02:00.453
- [sighs] It's not my--
- Well. well. well.

39
00:02:00.454 --> 00:02:03.706
Is this Rainey Street or Electric Avenue?

40
00:02:03.707 --> 00:02:06.375
Are you going to take it higher. Hank?

41
00:02:06.376 --> 00:02:08.794
Are you going to take it higher?

42
00:02:08.795 --> 00:02:11.088
- [groaning]
- Stop getting him riled up. Dale.

43
00:02:11.089 --> 00:02:14.342
It is not our truck.
and I was just telling Hank

44
00:02:14.343 --> 00:02:16.052
no one will assume it is.

45
00:02:16.053 --> 00:02:18.137
Nice truck. Mr. Hill!

46
00:02:18.138 --> 00:02:20.348
Damn you. Luke Junior!

47
00:02:20.349 --> 00:02:23.017
- [♪ upbeat music playing]
- [food sizzling]

48
00:02:23.018 --> 00:02:25.270
- [chit printer rustling]
- [bell dinging]

49
00:02:27.689 --> 00:02:30.734
[pan sizzling]

50
00:02:32.486 --> 00:02:34.571
- Gomashio?
- On your right.

51
00:02:35.530 --> 00:02:37.948
- Caraway?
- On your left.

52
00:02:37.949 --> 00:02:39.909
- Ready for sauce. but just a--
- Drizzle.

53
00:02:39.910 --> 00:02:42.537
- I got you. Bobby.
- I know you do.

54
00:02:43.789 --> 00:02:46.791
I was thinkin' maybe after this.
if you've got things covered.

55
00:02:46.792 --> 00:02:50.294
I could make a...
[whispers] special delivery.

56
00:02:50.295 --> 00:02:51.962
Get outta here.
Go see your girl.

57
00:02:51.963 --> 00:02:54.507
Are you sure?
Because I could stay.

58
00:02:54.508 --> 00:02:56.133
You shouldn't work so much.

59
00:02:56.134 --> 00:02:58.344
When I was your age.
I was sneaking outta my job

60
00:02:58.345 --> 00:03:00.012
all the time to see my girlfriend.

61
00:03:00.013 --> 00:03:03.307
And then. I was sneaking outta her house
to see my other girlfriend.

62
00:03:03.308 --> 00:03:06.352
And then. they both found out.
so I was sneaking everywhere.

63
00:03:06.353 --> 00:03:09.146
[♪ gentle guitar music playing]

64
00:03:09.147 --> 00:03:10.690
[students chattering]

65
00:03:10.691 --> 00:03:12.401
- Hello?
- [Connie giggles]

66
00:03:13.485 --> 00:03:17.488
I thought you were "up to your ears
in Shishito Schnitzel."

67
00:03:17.489 --> 00:03:20.366
I am. but I knew you
had to study all week.

68
00:03:20.367 --> 00:03:23.327
and I needed my Connie fix.

69
00:03:23.328 --> 00:03:25.746
[♪ "I Think We're Alone Now"
by Tiffany playing]

70
00:03:25.747 --> 00:03:27.832
<i>- You don't understand.</i>
- [audience laughing]

71
00:03:27.833 --> 00:03:29.750
[Bobby laughing]

72
00:03:29.751 --> 00:03:31.919
He's right. we don't understand!

73
00:03:31.920 --> 00:03:33.629
<i>♪ Alone now ♪</i>

74
00:03:33.630 --> 00:03:37.300
<i>♪ There doesn't seem
to be anyone around ♪</i>

75
00:03:38.301 --> 00:03:41.345
<i>- ♪ I think we're alone now ♪</i>
- [beeping and whirring]

76
00:03:41.346 --> 00:03:42.471
[flame whooshing]

77
00:03:42.472 --> 00:03:44.306
[sugar crackling]

78
00:03:44.307 --> 00:03:47.309
<i>♪ I think we're alone now ♪</i>

79
00:03:47.310 --> 00:03:51.021
<i>♪ There doesn't seem
to be anyone around ♪</i>

80
00:03:51.022 --> 00:03:53.275
[camera clicking]

81
00:03:54.609 --> 00:03:56.902
Okay. that's it.

82
00:03:56.903 --> 00:04:00.448
This would be a crime to not share
how hot we are with the world.

83
00:04:00.449 --> 00:04:02.742
Are you sure you wanna do
a hard launch?

84
00:04:02.743 --> 00:04:05.828
Yes.
What's a hard launch?

85
00:04:05.829 --> 00:04:07.371
Okay. so a soft launch

86
00:04:07.372 --> 00:04:09.623
is posting a picture
of two wine glasses

87
00:04:09.624 --> 00:04:12.835
and saying. "Date night
with someone special" or whatever.

88
00:04:12.836 --> 00:04:16.630
Ooh. I'm intrigued.
Who's this other person?

89
00:04:16.631 --> 00:04:19.133
Exactly.
But a hard launch

90
00:04:19.134 --> 00:04:21.260
means you just put your relationship
out there.

91
00:04:21.261 --> 00:04:24.638
Everybody's gonna have an opinion.
Even exes.

92
00:04:24.639 --> 00:04:26.307
You have nothing to worry about.

93
00:04:26.308 --> 00:04:28.309
Rihanna's got a family now.

94
00:04:28.310 --> 00:04:31.270
- She has moved on from me.
- [Connie laughs]

95
00:04:31.271 --> 00:04:34.648
I just don't want things
to be weird with you and Chane.

96
00:04:34.649 --> 00:04:38.152
Oh. right.
Do you think he'll really care?

97
00:04:38.153 --> 00:04:42.114
He punched one of his frat brothers
for drinking from his water bottle.

98
00:04:42.115 --> 00:04:44.826
Okay. soft launch. it is.

99
00:04:46.036 --> 00:04:48.412
[♪ gentle guitar music playing]

100
00:04:48.413 --> 00:04:49.706
[camera clicking]

101
00:04:51.166 --> 00:04:52.209
[chiming]

102
00:04:54.169 --> 00:04:57.296
- [♪ gentle guitar music playing]
- [Dale puffing]

103
00:04:57.297 --> 00:05:00.007
It still has dealer plates.

104
00:05:00.008 --> 00:05:02.635
Probably some billionaire from California

105
00:05:02.636 --> 00:05:05.513
trying to escape
their oppressive state taxes.

106
00:05:05.514 --> 00:05:09.892
Or maybe it's an attractive woman
in those lady yoga pants.

107
00:05:09.893 --> 00:05:11.685
I think I love her.

108
00:05:11.686 --> 00:05:14.438
Let's see if they left any clues
that might be useful.

109
00:05:14.439 --> 00:05:16.774
- [♪ suspenseful music playing]
- Approach at your own risk.

110
00:05:16.775 --> 00:05:20.528
Lithium rays from EV batteries
cause sterilization.

111
00:05:20.529 --> 00:05:24.366
and who knows when Nancy's gonna
wanna give Joseph a sibling.

112
00:05:25.617 --> 00:05:27.576
- [car dash beeping]
- [Bill shrieks]

113
00:05:27.577 --> 00:05:31.497
Why does it have an eye. Hank?
What does it see?

114
00:05:31.498 --> 00:05:33.082
Everything!

115
00:05:33.083 --> 00:05:35.376
Ah. it's just some anti-theft thing.

116
00:05:35.377 --> 00:05:37.795
We musta triggered it
by gettin' too close.

117
00:05:37.796 --> 00:05:40.172
Balloon!
That's a clue.

118
00:05:40.173 --> 00:05:42.049
Maybe they just had a baby girl.

119
00:05:42.050 --> 00:05:44.510
<i>If</i> they believe in gender.

120
00:05:44.511 --> 00:05:47.346
Water. See?
Knew it was a woman!

121
00:05:47.347 --> 00:05:50.641
[Hank Hill] A back pillow.
Huh. probably sore

122
00:05:50.642 --> 00:05:53.060
from duckin' into
one of their safe spaces.

123
00:05:53.061 --> 00:05:55.229
[Bill Dauterive] Tote bag.
Tote bag. Ooh!

124
00:05:55.230 --> 00:05:57.481
Maybe she was gonna go get vegetables

125
00:05:57.482 --> 00:06:00.526
at the farmer's market
on the way home from work.

126
00:06:00.527 --> 00:06:02.945
because she's a busy
professional single mom.

127
00:06:02.946 --> 00:06:06.991
who gives her sons everything.
except the one thing she can't--

128
00:06:06.992 --> 00:06:08.868
a male influence.

129
00:06:08.869 --> 00:06:10.870
Keep it in your pants. Bill.

130
00:06:10.871 --> 00:06:13.622
- We don't know it's a woman.
- Dale's right.

131
00:06:13.623 --> 00:06:15.958
We don't even know if it's human.

132
00:06:15.959 --> 00:06:18.502
- Dale's wrong.
- Amateurs.

133
00:06:18.503 --> 00:06:20.546
You will never figure it out this way.

134
00:06:20.547 --> 00:06:24.300
As someone who has read
every mystery novel at the Book Barn.

135
00:06:24.301 --> 00:06:27.428
I know that you need
to approach each case

136
00:06:27.429 --> 00:06:29.388
with evidence-based reason.

137
00:06:29.389 --> 00:06:32.224
Only then will we solve this murder.

138
00:06:32.225 --> 00:06:35.269
Your theory is that the driver
was murdered?

139
00:06:35.270 --> 00:06:37.146
It cannot be ruled out.

140
00:06:37.147 --> 00:06:40.816
Okay. Peggy. we'll take all
of your theories into consideration.

141
00:06:40.817 --> 00:06:43.152
- I won't.
- Well. then. I will figure it out

142
00:06:43.153 --> 00:06:46.572
on my own and leave you
and the Scooby gang alone.

143
00:06:46.573 --> 00:06:49.366
Maybe you'll find out
it's a g-g-g-ghost!

144
00:06:49.367 --> 00:06:51.493
[laughing]

145
00:06:51.494 --> 00:06:53.787
Well. we've stood here long enough.

146
00:06:53.788 --> 00:06:56.165
I think it's time to escalate things.

147
00:06:56.166 --> 00:06:57.458
I say we...

148
00:06:57.459 --> 00:06:58.542
[♪ dramatic music plays]

149
00:06:58.543 --> 00:06:59.920
...leave a note.

150
00:07:01.671 --> 00:07:03.339
- "Dear sir--"
- Can you write.

151
00:07:03.340 --> 00:07:07.092
"If you're an attractive woman.
call Bill." and leave my number?

152
00:07:07.093 --> 00:07:09.470
Actually. you don't have
to say "attractive."

153
00:07:09.471 --> 00:07:13.432
I'm not writing any of that.
but this doesn't seem right either.

154
00:07:13.433 --> 00:07:15.726
"Dear Electric Truck Owner..."

155
00:07:15.727 --> 00:07:19.396
I cannot in good conscience
call that a truck.

156
00:07:19.397 --> 00:07:22.775
You boys still haven't figured it out yet.
Ruh-roh!

157
00:07:22.776 --> 00:07:24.735
Peggy. please.
You haven't either.

158
00:07:24.736 --> 00:07:26.070
No. but I will.

159
00:07:26.071 --> 00:07:28.530
I have been narrowing
down the possibilities

160
00:07:28.531 --> 00:07:31.075
by using a deduction chart.

161
00:07:31.076 --> 00:07:33.452
Everything you do is homework.

162
00:07:33.453 --> 00:07:34.787
Thank you.

163
00:07:34.788 --> 00:07:37.873
Well. at least you're not tryin'
to prove it's a murder anymore.

164
00:07:37.874 --> 00:07:40.125
I have crossed out that theory.

165
00:07:40.126 --> 00:07:44.713
My deduction chart tells me
it might just be manslaughter.

166
00:07:44.714 --> 00:07:46.840
Manslaughter most foul.

167
00:07:46.841 --> 00:07:51.470
You're sure you want to address
a potential criminal as "Dear"?

168
00:07:51.471 --> 00:07:52.972
Let's just start over.

169
00:07:52.973 --> 00:07:54.139
♪

170
00:07:54.140 --> 00:07:56.433
Okay. I think we cracked it.

171
00:07:56.434 --> 00:08:00.145
[clearing throat]
"To electric vehicle owner.

172
00:08:00.146 --> 00:08:02.606
"please move your vehicle.

173
00:08:02.607 --> 00:08:04.233
From. Hank Hill."

174
00:08:04.234 --> 00:08:06.694
I still think we should sign it. "Love."

175
00:08:06.695 --> 00:08:09.113
Man. you talkin' 'bout
a dang ol'-- just sad. man.

176
00:08:09.114 --> 00:08:10.364
[insects chirping]

177
00:08:10.365 --> 00:08:13.076
[ominous humming]

178
00:08:15.161 --> 00:08:18.498
[♪ country guitar music playing]

179
00:08:20.834 --> 00:08:23.335
Where's Bobby?
Doesn't he. like. live here?

180
00:08:23.336 --> 00:08:26.005
Delivery. He'll be back soon.

181
00:08:26.006 --> 00:08:28.590
Finally.
You know how long I've been waiting?

182
00:08:28.591 --> 00:08:31.385
You gotta tell me.
Who's this fat-fingered [bleep]

183
00:08:31.386 --> 00:08:32.761
Connie's soft launching?

184
00:08:32.762 --> 00:08:36.515
Huh?
Connie's dating someone?

185
00:08:36.516 --> 00:08:38.809
You didn't know?
Aren't you guys friends?

186
00:08:38.810 --> 00:08:42.646
Sure. but we don't talk about
who she's dating.

187
00:08:42.647 --> 00:08:44.565
or their fingers and stuff.

188
00:08:44.566 --> 00:08:48.694
We talk about platonic things
like politics and horses.

189
00:08:48.695 --> 00:08:49.862
[♪ suspicious music playing]

190
00:08:49.863 --> 00:08:51.698
Lemme see your hands.

191
00:08:53.033 --> 00:08:55.242
[♪ suspicious music continues]

192
00:08:55.243 --> 00:08:56.994
- I'm dating Connie.
- [both] What?!

193
00:08:56.995 --> 00:08:59.538
I'm sorry. man.
I know she was your girl.

194
00:08:59.539 --> 00:09:00.998
but I'm crazy about her.

195
00:09:00.999 --> 00:09:02.916
Tell me one thing about her.

196
00:09:02.917 --> 00:09:05.127
She's... Asian.

197
00:09:05.128 --> 00:09:08.172
- What kind of Asian?
- My favorite kind?

198
00:09:08.173 --> 00:09:09.840
Yeah. you're fired.

199
00:09:09.841 --> 00:09:11.175
Whoa. whoa. whoa!

200
00:09:11.176 --> 00:09:14.428
Emilio isn't dating Connie.
I am.

201
00:09:14.429 --> 00:09:18.140
Emilio was just covering for me
because he's got my back.

202
00:09:18.141 --> 00:09:22.478
That's why I can actually leave
the restaurant every once in a while.

203
00:09:22.479 --> 00:09:24.354
At least now you're being honest.

204
00:09:24.355 --> 00:09:27.024
So. no hard feelings?

205
00:09:27.025 --> 00:09:29.943
No hard feelings.
But you're still fired.

206
00:09:29.944 --> 00:09:31.487
- Why?
- What?!

207
00:09:31.488 --> 00:09:33.155
For covering for Bobby.

208
00:09:33.156 --> 00:09:36.075
It's called Robata Chane.
not Robata Liars.

209
00:09:36.076 --> 00:09:38.911
Oh. no!
Guess you won't be able to sneak off

210
00:09:38.912 --> 00:09:41.497
to see Connie
for your dirty little nooners.

211
00:09:41.498 --> 00:09:44.374
She has class at noon.
[groaning]

212
00:09:44.375 --> 00:09:45.376
♪

213
00:09:47.378 --> 00:09:49.213
You can't fire Emilio.

214
00:09:49.214 --> 00:09:52.174
I know you're pissed at me.
but you and Connie broke up.

215
00:09:52.175 --> 00:09:53.675
Why do you even care?

216
00:09:53.676 --> 00:09:57.346
I don't. obviously.
Losing him is just good for business.

217
00:09:57.347 --> 00:10:00.808
Do you think Kylie Jenner
cares about any of her Emilios?

218
00:10:00.809 --> 00:10:03.977
What am I supposed to do now?
We've got customers coming.

219
00:10:03.978 --> 00:10:06.897
Please.
I can go to the border. throw a rock.

220
00:10:06.898 --> 00:10:09.733
and hit two Emilios
who we can pay way less.

221
00:10:09.734 --> 00:10:11.902
I learned that in business school.

222
00:10:11.903 --> 00:10:15.323
They have a class
on throwing rocks at Mexicans?

223
00:10:16.074 --> 00:10:18.992
I'm so sorry.
You're the Goose to my Maverick.

224
00:10:18.993 --> 00:10:22.579
and I was sayin' that
before they rebooted the franchise.

225
00:10:22.580 --> 00:10:25.582
Still haven't seen it.
But now. I guess I have time.

226
00:10:25.583 --> 00:10:29.378
I'll get Chane to hire you back.
Please. don't take another job.

227
00:10:29.379 --> 00:10:32.464
Okay. but I can't go that long
without working.

228
00:10:32.465 --> 00:10:35.468
Last time. I got really into ceramics
and day drinking.

229
00:10:37.428 --> 00:10:39.639
- Bwah!
- There's a new note. Hank.

230
00:10:41.766 --> 00:10:45.769
"Dear Mr. Hill.
the streets belong to all of us.

231
00:10:45.770 --> 00:10:48.313
"Let's find a way to coexist.

232
00:10:48.314 --> 00:10:49.773
Namaste."

233
00:10:49.774 --> 00:10:52.651
Her name is Namaste.

234
00:10:52.652 --> 00:10:55.863
No. that's not... [sighs]
I-It's a yoga word.

235
00:10:55.864 --> 00:10:57.447
As we suspected!

236
00:10:57.448 --> 00:11:00.701
A commie
who dabbles in the dark arts.

237
00:11:00.702 --> 00:11:04.705
Well. I'd like to give them a talking to.
but I gotta find 'em first.

238
00:11:04.706 --> 00:11:07.833
Wait a minute.
They're gonna have to move it by 6 a.m.

239
00:11:07.834 --> 00:11:09.251
or risk getting towed.

240
00:11:09.252 --> 00:11:13.547
And when they do. we'll be here
on a good old-fashioned stakeout.

241
00:11:13.548 --> 00:11:14.923
- Ooh! Yay!
- Woo-hoo!

242
00:11:14.924 --> 00:11:16.383
- A stakeout.
- Yeah. man. 'lil stakeout time.

243
00:11:16.384 --> 00:11:19.761
I'll bring the beef jerky
and night vision goggles!

244
00:11:19.762 --> 00:11:22.973
Okay. guys. well.
let's reconvene and. uh...

245
00:11:22.974 --> 00:11:25.392
Well. we're already standing here.

246
00:11:25.393 --> 00:11:27.060
Stakeout starts now.

247
00:11:27.061 --> 00:11:28.395
♪

248
00:11:28.396 --> 00:11:32.524
Ugh.
Do you have <i>any</i> restaurant skills?

249
00:11:32.525 --> 00:11:35.194
No. but I was a prison guard
in Venezuela.

250
00:11:35.195 --> 00:11:37.196
so I've served many last meals.

251
00:11:37.197 --> 00:11:39.114
Murderers love pizza.

252
00:11:39.115 --> 00:11:41.992
- I like pizza.
- Watch out for this guy. eh?

253
00:11:41.993 --> 00:11:45.787
- [groaning]
- [laughs] Well. good luck.

254
00:11:45.788 --> 00:11:48.081
You can't leave me with all this.

255
00:11:48.082 --> 00:11:51.377
Oh. shit!
I hope you and Connie didn't have plans.

256
00:11:53.546 --> 00:11:55.548
[food sizzling. plates clattering]

257
00:11:56.633 --> 00:12:00.010
- Gomashio?
- No. Marcelo.

258
00:12:00.011 --> 00:12:02.262
Hey. Bobby. I cooked the fish.

259
00:12:02.263 --> 00:12:04.848
- That was sashimi!
- Smells good. right?

260
00:12:04.849 --> 00:12:06.892
[groaning]
You cooked all of it?

261
00:12:06.893 --> 00:12:08.810
It's supposed to be served raw.

262
00:12:08.811 --> 00:12:11.481
Uh-oh.
I'll take out the trash.

263
00:12:12.982 --> 00:12:15.985
[♪ somber guitar music playing]

264
00:12:19.948 --> 00:12:22.074
- [both] Mwah.
- I only have 20 minutes

265
00:12:22.075 --> 00:12:25.994
before I have to meet my lab partner.
but I miss your face so much.

266
00:12:25.995 --> 00:12:27.996
I know what that's like.

267
00:12:27.997 --> 00:12:30.499
You're talking about Emilio. aren't you?

268
00:12:30.500 --> 00:12:32.209
[sighs] Yeah.

269
00:12:32.210 --> 00:12:35.212
And you!
But Chane won't hire him back.

270
00:12:35.213 --> 00:12:39.800
Chane is only scared of two things.
the Babadook and his father.

271
00:12:39.801 --> 00:12:42.219
I bet Ted would like to hear
about how his son

272
00:12:42.220 --> 00:12:44.054
is tanking his investment.

273
00:12:44.055 --> 00:12:47.349
Chane will hate me if I call his dad.

274
00:12:47.350 --> 00:12:49.559
Do you want Emilio back or not?

275
00:12:49.560 --> 00:12:52.271
- [glass shattering]
- [cooks screaming]

276
00:12:52.272 --> 00:12:54.690
- Yeah. I'm gonna call Ted.
- [smoke alarm beeping]

277
00:12:54.691 --> 00:12:56.317
[♪ banjo playing]

278
00:12:56.943 --> 00:13:00.153
Can you play <i>Dust in the Wind</i> next?

279
00:13:00.154 --> 00:13:04.658
Well. he only has two hands
and that song has two guitar parts.

280
00:13:04.659 --> 00:13:06.326
I'll go get my strings.

281
00:13:06.327 --> 00:13:08.620
And can you bring some tissues too?

282
00:13:08.621 --> 00:13:13.166
- That song always makes me cry.
- Dang ol' empties. man.

283
00:13:13.167 --> 00:13:15.168
Talkin' 'bout a-- just like
a salt and savory man.

284
00:13:15.169 --> 00:13:17.754
Alamo like a dang ol'
palate cleanser. man.

285
00:13:17.755 --> 00:13:20.173
I may have drunk most of those.

286
00:13:20.174 --> 00:13:24.219
It's been ages since I had an excuse
to take a whiz outside.

287
00:13:24.220 --> 00:13:28.181
Wind in my hair. the moonlight
on my tallywacker.

288
00:13:28.182 --> 00:13:30.892
- Watch the truck.
- On it!

289
00:13:30.893 --> 00:13:33.604
- [♪ ominous music plays]
- [crickets chirping]

290
00:13:35.231 --> 00:13:37.983
- [♪ somber guitar music playing]
- Just... me...

291
00:13:37.984 --> 00:13:39.152
[Bill whimpering]

292
00:13:40.069 --> 00:13:41.404
[Bill snoring]

293
00:13:43.906 --> 00:13:47.035
It just may be time
to admit defeat. Peggy Hill.

294
00:13:48.411 --> 00:13:50.287
- [Dale shouting]
- Idiot.

295
00:13:50.288 --> 00:13:52.165
[snoring] Oh! Oh. no.

296
00:13:52.874 --> 00:13:54.666
- Oh. thank God.
- [crickets chirping]

297
00:13:54.667 --> 00:13:56.710
- [truck beeping]
- [Bill gasps]

298
00:13:56.711 --> 00:13:58.962
- [electric truck humming]
- [exclaiming] Hank!

299
00:13:58.963 --> 00:14:02.466
[muffled] Dale! Boomhauer!

300
00:14:02.467 --> 00:14:04.551
The truck dematerialized!

301
00:14:04.552 --> 00:14:06.636
No. it's just over there now.

302
00:14:06.637 --> 00:14:08.430
What happened?
Who moved it?

303
00:14:08.431 --> 00:14:11.641
- It moved... itself.
- It what?!

304
00:14:11.642 --> 00:14:14.770
I know how that sounds.
but that's what I saw.

305
00:14:14.771 --> 00:14:17.230
Dang it. Bill.
you must have fallen asleep.

306
00:14:17.231 --> 00:14:20.150
What if that was our last chance
to catch this degenerate?

307
00:14:20.151 --> 00:14:23.904
I'm sorry. fellas.
I failed you all.

308
00:14:23.905 --> 00:14:25.739
Unless I'm still asleep.

309
00:14:25.740 --> 00:14:27.991
- [hand smacking]
- Ow! No. I'm awake.

310
00:14:27.992 --> 00:14:29.618
♪

311
00:14:29.619 --> 00:14:33.288
Sir. your son fired our best employee.

312
00:14:33.289 --> 00:14:35.207
Yeah?
Well. I should have fired you!

313
00:14:35.208 --> 00:14:36.750
Dad?

314
00:14:36.751 --> 00:14:38.251
[lowers voice]
Fire Bobby.

315
00:14:38.252 --> 00:14:40.754
If you're gonna fire anybody.
fire Chane.

316
00:14:40.755 --> 00:14:42.631
All he does is bring his frat bros in

317
00:14:42.632 --> 00:14:44.257
- for free sake bombs.
- [Ted sighing]

318
00:14:44.258 --> 00:14:48.261
All you do is sneak out
to deliver snacks to my sloppy seconds.

319
00:14:48.262 --> 00:14:51.223
- Oh. we're going there?
- I'm already there!

320
00:14:51.224 --> 00:14:53.809
Well. I'm gonna go there. too.

321
00:14:53.810 --> 00:14:55.352
Come on. let's do this!

322
00:14:55.353 --> 00:14:57.813
Enough. enough!
I'm not a marriage counselor.

323
00:14:57.814 --> 00:15:00.107
Chane. you begged me
to buy into this restaurant.

324
00:15:00.108 --> 00:15:01.942
and I thought. "Well. at least
he doesn't wanna be

325
00:15:01.943 --> 00:15:03.819
a professional snowboarder anymore."

326
00:15:03.820 --> 00:15:07.823
But the best way to learn any business
is from the ground up.

327
00:15:07.824 --> 00:15:09.449
I started in the mail room.

328
00:15:09.450 --> 00:15:11.910
Whoa. Dad.
You were poor?

329
00:15:11.911 --> 00:15:15.956
I thought it was helping you.
but it's turned you into... this.

330
00:15:15.957 --> 00:15:18.542
- Rude.
- But true.

331
00:15:18.543 --> 00:15:20.168
You can't let this business fail.

332
00:15:20.169 --> 00:15:23.088
That's why you're going to take
Emilio's place in the kitchen.

333
00:15:23.089 --> 00:15:24.298
- Me?
- Him?!

334
00:15:25.800 --> 00:15:28.885
You sure you don't wanna be
a professional snowboarder?

335
00:15:28.886 --> 00:15:30.596
It is not too late.

336
00:15:32.598 --> 00:15:35.434
- [♪ upbeat percussion music playing]
- [knife thudding]

337
00:15:35.435 --> 00:15:37.437
- [stove top sizzling]
- [liquid bubbling]

338
00:15:37.979 --> 00:15:38.980
[metal lid clanking]

339
00:15:39.647 --> 00:15:40.856
[bell dinging]

340
00:15:40.857 --> 00:15:44.317
Table five is threatening to leave
unless they get their miso-wursts!

341
00:15:44.318 --> 00:15:46.278
They're coming!
It's all coming.

342
00:15:46.279 --> 00:15:48.780
I had an egg right here.
Where'd it go?

343
00:15:48.781 --> 00:15:51.491
Nobody took your egg. Bobby.
Get over it.

344
00:15:51.492 --> 00:15:55.454
Like how I got over missing
Naval Battle Night at my frat tonight.

345
00:15:55.455 --> 00:15:57.122
They flooded the entire basement.

346
00:15:57.123 --> 00:16:01.042
Sounds cool.
Your next party theme can be toxic mold.

347
00:16:01.043 --> 00:16:02.711
And you think I wanna be here?

348
00:16:02.712 --> 00:16:05.046
I'm supposed to be at the movies
with my girlfriend.

349
00:16:05.047 --> 00:16:07.299
Make it make sense why she's with you.

350
00:16:07.300 --> 00:16:10.135
You have no muscle definition.
Your car sucks.

351
00:16:10.136 --> 00:16:12.929
I'm talking. like. zero muscle definition.

352
00:16:12.930 --> 00:16:17.100
Did you ever think that maybe
I'm just a better boyfriend?

353
00:16:17.101 --> 00:16:19.060
[bleep] no. Hey!

354
00:16:19.061 --> 00:16:21.062
- Don't walk away from me!
- I'm not.

355
00:16:21.063 --> 00:16:22.981
I'm getting eggs!

356
00:16:22.982 --> 00:16:24.191
[door thudding]

357
00:16:24.192 --> 00:16:26.902
There's no way
you're a better boyfriend than me.

358
00:16:26.903 --> 00:16:28.987
You were seeing multiple women.

359
00:16:28.988 --> 00:16:30.322
- Jealous?
- No.

360
00:16:30.323 --> 00:16:32.407
All you cared about was sex.

361
00:16:32.408 --> 00:16:34.701
At first. yeah. because she was hot.

362
00:16:34.702 --> 00:16:37.412
But sometimes after sex
we'd. like. talk and stuff.

363
00:16:37.413 --> 00:16:38.955
and it was just as good.

364
00:16:38.956 --> 00:16:42.959
It was like she made my heart
bust a nut.

365
00:16:42.960 --> 00:16:45.420
Really?
You caught feelin's?

366
00:16:45.421 --> 00:16:46.713
No!

367
00:16:46.714 --> 00:16:48.757
- [♪ gentle guitar music playing]
- Maybe.

368
00:16:48.758 --> 00:16:51.301
Dude. it's okay to say you did.

369
00:16:51.302 --> 00:16:53.720
You don't get it.
After we broke up.

370
00:16:53.721 --> 00:16:55.847
I kinda went ham
and asked her to marry me.

371
00:16:55.848 --> 00:16:58.433
Wait. what?
You proposed?

372
00:16:58.434 --> 00:17:01.686
- Like down on one knee?
- Stop making a big deal out of it.

373
00:17:01.687 --> 00:17:03.396
It is a huge deal!

374
00:17:03.397 --> 00:17:06.608
It doesn't matter.
It was a dumb simp move.

375
00:17:06.609 --> 00:17:09.236
She said she never wants to get married.

376
00:17:09.237 --> 00:17:11.821
What? Did she say why?

377
00:17:11.822 --> 00:17:14.699
I didn't ask.
I mean. who rejects these abs?

378
00:17:14.700 --> 00:17:16.826
Maybe she's not into abs.

379
00:17:16.827 --> 00:17:18.412
Yeah. that's pretty clear now.

380
00:17:19.956 --> 00:17:22.541
I'm sorry. Chane.
I should have let you know

381
00:17:22.542 --> 00:17:24.793
before me and Connie soft launched.

382
00:17:24.794 --> 00:17:26.127
Thank you!

383
00:17:26.128 --> 00:17:28.630
Who knew you were such a hand detective?

384
00:17:28.631 --> 00:17:30.257
Whatever. I don't even care.

385
00:17:30.258 --> 00:17:32.300
Good luck in your dead-end relationship.

386
00:17:32.301 --> 00:17:34.219
- [doorknob rattling]
- What the hell? It's locked.

387
00:17:34.220 --> 00:17:36.638
It does that.
I usually prop it.

388
00:17:36.639 --> 00:17:38.766
but somebody was distracting me.

389
00:17:39.433 --> 00:17:41.101
[doors rattling]

390
00:17:41.102 --> 00:17:43.061
[Bobby grunting]

391
00:17:43.062 --> 00:17:45.355
Dammit. we're gonna be
locked down here forever.

392
00:17:45.356 --> 00:17:47.148
I don't wanna have to eat you. Bobby.

393
00:17:47.149 --> 00:17:50.402
We're literally surrounded
by months' worth of food.

394
00:17:50.403 --> 00:17:53.572
- I don't know what this stuff is!
- Idiot.

395
00:17:53.573 --> 00:17:55.282
Does anyone have a key?

396
00:17:55.283 --> 00:17:57.367
Yeah. but you're not gonna like it.

397
00:17:57.368 --> 00:17:58.702
[key jingling]

398
00:17:58.703 --> 00:18:02.122
[Bobby Hill] Emilio!
My sweet. sweet man!

399
00:18:02.123 --> 00:18:05.333
- Thank you for comin' so fast.
- We need you back. man.

400
00:18:05.334 --> 00:18:07.502
You can start right after you let us out.

401
00:18:07.503 --> 00:18:10.505
- Really?
- Yeah. Working here sucks.

402
00:18:10.506 --> 00:18:11.840
- You can have it.
- [Bobby exclaiming]

403
00:18:11.841 --> 00:18:14.342
I don't know.
I'd love to come back.

404
00:18:14.343 --> 00:18:17.429
but I'm fielding a lot of offers
from Michelin Star places.

405
00:18:17.430 --> 00:18:18.930
We'll give you a raise.

406
00:18:18.931 --> 00:18:20.765
- [Emilio] How big?
- Twenty percent?

407
00:18:20.766 --> 00:18:22.142
- Ten percent.
- [Emilio] Twenty-five.

408
00:18:22.143 --> 00:18:25.061
I'm also gonna need a title bump
to Executive Sous Chef.

409
00:18:25.062 --> 00:18:28.440
And on Thursday nights. my Steely Dan
cover band gets to play here.

410
00:18:28.441 --> 00:18:31.651
I hate Steely Dan.
I don't even know what genre it is.

411
00:18:31.652 --> 00:18:34.404
That's the first thing
we've agreed on all night.

412
00:18:34.405 --> 00:18:36.406
Is it jazz?
What is it?

413
00:18:36.407 --> 00:18:38.908
- Whole lotta restaurants in Dallas.
- [Bobby] Fine. fine.

414
00:18:38.909 --> 00:18:41.536
- Just get us outta here!
- [door unlocking]

415
00:18:41.537 --> 00:18:43.038
- [birds chirping]
- [dog barking]

416
00:18:43.039 --> 00:18:46.750
Turns out. Bill was right.
He wasn't seeing things.

417
00:18:46.751 --> 00:18:48.960
This model can be operated remotely.

418
00:18:48.961 --> 00:18:52.213
as long as the driver
is within a 200-foot radius.

419
00:18:52.214 --> 00:18:53.965
Sorcery!

420
00:18:53.966 --> 00:18:56.718
Also. the doors automatically open

421
00:18:56.719 --> 00:18:58.887
when the driver is within three feet.

422
00:18:58.888 --> 00:19:01.640
which I admit is kind of a neat feature.
if your hands

423
00:19:01.641 --> 00:19:06.478
are full carrying tools.
fertilizer. or-- or whatnot.

424
00:19:06.479 --> 00:19:08.647
Electric cars are stupid.

425
00:19:08.648 --> 00:19:12.359
Now. this circle
marks our 200-foot radius.

426
00:19:12.360 --> 00:19:16.738
The culprit is somewhere in this circle
lurking like a coward.

427
00:19:16.739 --> 00:19:17.906
[marker squeaking]

428
00:19:17.907 --> 00:19:20.951
Okay. time for the final reveal.

429
00:19:22.536 --> 00:19:25.163
Now. if one of you
finds him before I do.

430
00:19:25.164 --> 00:19:27.123
don't engage. wait for me.

431
00:19:27.124 --> 00:19:29.668
If it's a woman.
can I compliment her eyes?

432
00:19:29.669 --> 00:19:32.253
If you want to flush out
the owner of this car.

433
00:19:32.254 --> 00:19:34.172
you just need to set off the alarm.

434
00:19:34.173 --> 00:19:37.008
- [♪ suspenseful music playing]
- Now. wait just--

435
00:19:37.009 --> 00:19:38.760
- Peggy. no!
- [truck beeping]

436
00:19:38.761 --> 00:19:39.844
[door whirring]

437
00:19:39.845 --> 00:19:41.846
Dale?
This is your truck?

438
00:19:41.847 --> 00:19:44.265
Actually. it's Nancy's.

439
00:19:44.266 --> 00:19:47.435
And I bet you all wanna know
how I figured that out.

440
00:19:47.436 --> 00:19:50.480
Actually. I'd like to hear Dale
explain why he just let us--

441
00:19:50.481 --> 00:19:52.941
I admit. until a few moments ago.

442
00:19:52.942 --> 00:19:55.485
I was struggling just like you.

443
00:19:55.486 --> 00:19:58.780
<i>But like any great detective.
which I am...</i>

444
00:19:58.781 --> 00:20:01.282
- [phone ringing]
<i>- ...I had a stroke of inspiration.</i>

445
00:20:01.283 --> 00:20:03.910
[Nancy Gribble] [on phone]
<i>Hey. Sug. did you see my new truck?</i>

446
00:20:03.911 --> 00:20:06.413
Yes. it's electric.
and I know what you're thinking.

447
00:20:06.414 --> 00:20:09.124
But the producers of my show
got it for me as a gift.

448
00:20:09.125 --> 00:20:11.584
Isn't that cherry red to die for?

449
00:20:11.585 --> 00:20:13.753
- Hm.
- [♪ mischievous violin music playing]

450
00:20:13.754 --> 00:20:17.465
- Okay. time for the final reveal.
- [marker squeaking]

451
00:20:17.466 --> 00:20:19.676
It all makes perfect sense.

452
00:20:19.677 --> 00:20:24.013
The balloon. just the sort of thing
you would receive if your show.

453
00:20:24.014 --> 00:20:27.434
<i>Selling Arlen.</i> got picked up
for another season.

454
00:20:27.435 --> 00:20:30.478
which brings us to the tote.

455
00:20:30.479 --> 00:20:32.021
Ooh!
[clapping]

456
00:20:32.022 --> 00:20:35.734
And the lumbar cushion?
I remember Nancy telling me

457
00:20:35.735 --> 00:20:38.862
how she threw out her back
after a night with--

458
00:20:38.863 --> 00:20:40.363
Actually. forget about that.

459
00:20:40.364 --> 00:20:42.991
And now. for the smoking gun.

460
00:20:42.992 --> 00:20:45.160
<i>While Dale was pretending to pee...</i>

461
00:20:45.161 --> 00:20:47.329
- [Dale exclaiming]
<i>- ...he actually was moving the car.</i>

462
00:20:49.248 --> 00:20:51.750
You're wrong.
I peed after.

463
00:20:51.751 --> 00:20:54.252
Peggy Hill rests her case.

464
00:20:54.253 --> 00:20:57.714
I was right.
It <i>was</i> a beautiful woman.

465
00:20:57.715 --> 00:20:59.924
Dale. why'd you lie to us?

466
00:20:59.925 --> 00:21:03.553
I knew you'd tease us
for being the kind of Positive Petes

467
00:21:03.554 --> 00:21:05.555
who would own an electric truck.

468
00:21:05.556 --> 00:21:09.225
But why didn't you park it
in front of your own dang house?

469
00:21:09.226 --> 00:21:12.479
That would make us targets
for burglars or hate crimes.

470
00:21:12.480 --> 00:21:14.522
Dammit. Dale.
It was bad enough

471
00:21:14.523 --> 00:21:18.693
when I thought a stranger did this to us.
but now I have to kick <i>your</i> ass.

472
00:21:18.694 --> 00:21:20.904
[gasps] You'll have to catch me first!

473
00:21:20.905 --> 00:21:22.530
- [Dale grunting]
- [truck humming]

474
00:21:22.531 --> 00:21:23.782
Ah!

475
00:21:23.783 --> 00:21:26.284
- [truck chiming. turning off]
- [Dale exclaiming]

476
00:21:26.285 --> 00:21:30.038
Nancy also asked me to charge it.
but I forgot.

477
00:21:30.039 --> 00:21:33.082
Another case cracked by Peggy Hill.

478
00:21:33.083 --> 00:21:35.001
You've only had one case.

479
00:21:35.002 --> 00:21:37.378
100% success rate.

480
00:21:37.379 --> 00:21:39.548
[students chattering]

481
00:21:40.925 --> 00:21:43.468
You're here?!
Oh. but how?

482
00:21:43.469 --> 00:21:45.804
Chane hired Emilio back.

483
00:21:45.805 --> 00:21:48.723
I wish I could say
I Jedi mind-tricked him.

484
00:21:48.724 --> 00:21:51.142
but he just hated doin' real work.

485
00:21:51.143 --> 00:21:53.311
You should have told him
it was good for his core.

486
00:21:53.312 --> 00:21:57.524
Oh. and. uh.
Chane said something interesting.

487
00:21:57.525 --> 00:21:59.442
Sounds impossible. but go on.

488
00:21:59.443 --> 00:22:01.987
Did he really propose to you?

489
00:22:03.280 --> 00:22:06.699
Oh. my God.
He was drunk and kind of spiraling.

490
00:22:06.700 --> 00:22:09.202
[laughing] I don't think
he'd ever been rejected before.

491
00:22:09.203 --> 00:22:13.331
Honestly. it felt kinda good
to pop that bubble for him.

492
00:22:13.332 --> 00:22:14.958
Well. that wasn't the interesting part.

493
00:22:14.959 --> 00:22:17.794
He said you never wanted to get married.

494
00:22:17.795 --> 00:22:19.546
Is that true?

495
00:22:19.547 --> 00:22:21.089
- [♪ gentle guitar music playing]
- Maybe.

496
00:22:21.090 --> 00:22:23.049
Ever since my parents got divorced.

497
00:22:23.050 --> 00:22:25.176
I don't know if I believe in marriage.

498
00:22:25.177 --> 00:22:27.595
It seems like
there's so many things we just do

499
00:22:27.596 --> 00:22:30.890
because that's what our parents did.
Does it bother you?

500
00:22:30.891 --> 00:22:34.185
No. Connie. we've only
been dating three weeks.

501
00:22:34.186 --> 00:22:37.689
I'm not some psycho
who wants to be a child bride.

502
00:22:37.690 --> 00:22:39.691
- Groom.
- [laughing] Groom.

503
00:22:39.692 --> 00:22:42.777
But eventually. maybe down the road.

504
00:22:42.778 --> 00:22:46.322
it'd be nice to know it's an option.

505
00:22:46.323 --> 00:22:49.785
- Ask me again in five years?
- You know I will.

506
00:22:51.036 --> 00:22:53.788
And. hey. now that Chane
knows about us...

507
00:22:53.789 --> 00:22:56.374
- [♪ bright music playing]
- [phone beeping]

508
00:22:56.375 --> 00:23:00.044
So. uh. how's Nancy liking her... truck?

509
00:23:00.045 --> 00:23:01.754
She likes it fine.

510
00:23:01.755 --> 00:23:04.883
John Redcorn installed
a charger at his place.

511
00:23:04.884 --> 00:23:08.428
Fine by me.
Let <i>his</i> electricity bill go up.

512
00:23:08.429 --> 00:23:11.097
I win again! Wingo!

513
00:23:11.098 --> 00:23:12.765
[phone buzzing]

514
00:23:12.766 --> 00:23:15.477
Huh. looks like
Bobby and Connie are official.

515
00:23:16.270 --> 00:23:17.437
Aww.

516
00:23:17.438 --> 00:23:19.439
Talkin' 'bout doin'
a dang ol' hard launch. man.

517
00:23:19.440 --> 00:23:22.066
Wonder why they took so long to tell us.

518
00:23:22.067 --> 00:23:24.612
[Minh Souphanousinphone]
No! Anyone but him!

519
00:23:25.863 --> 00:23:27.781
[Kahn Souphanousinphone]
Damn you. Bobby Hill!

520
00:23:28.782 --> 00:23:31.994
[♪ bluegrass version
of "Yahoos and Triangles" playing]

521
00:23:47.426 --> 00:23:49.720
<i>- ♪ Yee-haw! ♪
- ♪ Wa-hoo! ♪</i>

522
00:24:08.447 --> 00:24:09.530
[♪ song ends]

523
00:24:09.531 --> 00:24:10.615
[birds chirping]

524
00:24:10.616 --> 00:24:12.533
- [golf club thumps]
- [crowd cheering]

525
00:24:12.534 --> 00:24:14.577
♪

526
00:24:14.578 --> 00:24:16.120
[Chane Wassanasong]
<i>It's called Robata Chane.</i>

527
00:24:16.121 --> 00:24:17.580
<i>not Robata Liars.</i>

528
00:24:17.581 --> 00:24:20.501
[♪ fanfare playing]

528
00:24:21.305 --> 00:25:21.907
